text: Tian Koekemoer (born 21 September 1994) is a South African cricketer. He made his first-class debut for Eastern Province in the 2015–16 Sunfoil 3-Day Cup on 8 October 2015. In September 2018, he was named in Eastern Province's squad for the 2018 Africa T20 Cup. He was the leading run-scorer for Eastern Province in the 2018–19 CSA 3-Day Provincial Cup, with 697 runs in ten matches. ==References== ==External links== * Category:1994 births Category:Living people Category:South African cricketers Category:Eastern Province cricketers Category:Place of birth missing (living people)
